description: Coefficients of the '5th order' mock theta function F_0(q)
references: George E. Andrews, The fifth and seventh order mock theta functions, Trans. Amer. Math. Soc., 293 (1986) 113-134
George E. Andrews and Frank G. Garvan, Ramanujan's "lost" notebook VI: The mock theta conjectures, Advances in Mathematics, 73 (1989) 242-255
Srinivasa Ramanujan, Collected Papers, Chelsea, New York, 1962, pp. 354-355
Srinivasa Ramanujan, The Lost Notebook and Other Unpublished Papers, Narosa Publishing House, New Delhi, 1988, pp. 20, 22, 23, 25
George N. Watson, The mock theta functions (2), Proc. London Math. Soc., series 2, 42 (1937) 274-304
formula: G.f.: F_0(q) = sum for n >= 0 of q^(2n^2)/((1-q)(1-q^3)...(1-q^(2n-1)))a(n) = number of partitions of n into odd parts, each of which occurs at least twice, such that if k occurs then all smaller positive odd numbers occur
author: _Dean Hickerson_, Dec 19 1999
